Spots can be seen about a mile and a half out into the sea outside the major municipality of Hillsborough, but in fewer places than last week.
Algae blooms have also been observed in the municipality of Pasco.
Mean concentrations in or off the coast of Pinellas have been reported in the past week. Off the coast of Hillsborough low to high concentrations, background concentrations to high concentrations in Manatee, background concentrations to high concentrations in or off the coast of Sarasota, background concentrations to medium or high concentrations in the mountains.
Reports of respiratory irritation continue to come from the major municipalities of Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Lee and Collier.
There were no reports of respiratory irritation in northwest Florida last week.
